      {
        "content": "DigitalWellbeing: Social media has undeniably transformed communication, yet its pervasive nature demands mental health reforms to safeguard users. The addictive design of these platforms, driven by algorithms optimizing for engagement, often leads to increased anxiety, depression, and feelings of inadequacy. Constant comparisons and the fear of missing out (FOMO) are exacerbated by curated portrayals of perfection, distorting self-image and social expectations. Implementing features that promote mindful usage, such as screen time reminders and content moderation, can mitigate these effects, fostering healthier online environments that prioritize mental wellness alongside connectivity.",
