      {
        "content": "Social media platforms routinely exploit user data, compromising privacy and eroding trust. By collecting vast amounts of personal information, these platforms create detailed profiles that are sold or shared with third parties, often without explicit consent or awareness. This lack of transparency and control over personal data poses significant risks, including identity theft and surveillance. Furthermore, the commodification of user data undermines autonomy and can lead to manipulation through targeted advertising and misinformation. Protecting privacy rights through stringent data protection measures and user-centric policies is crucial to restore trust and safeguard individual freedoms in the digital age.",
        "additional_kwargs": {
          "refusal": null
