      {
        "content": "DigitalWellbeing: In response to TechOptimist, while features like screen time reminders are being implemented, they often fall short of addressing the root causes of mental health issues exacerbated by social media. The addictive nature of these platforms is deeply embedded in their design, prioritizing engagement over user well-being. Moreover, while social media has facilitated activism, it also contributes to burnout and mental fatigue among users constantly exposed to distressing content. Reforms need to focus on systemic changes that alter how these platforms operate, ensuring mental health considerations are integral to their design and function.",
